comment.narrative:
- The capacities of 9 civil society organizations were strengthened in gender intervention, including in terms of resilience building in the context of disaster/crisis, 
-Strengthened capacities of 17,687.00 women across 8 provinces of Angola in awareness and capacity building in political rights and civil participation and economic empowerment; 
- 234 girls, sex workers in the municipality of Lobito of Benguela province were supported to access social protection services;
- 40 women were empowered and became effective participants in local governance processes, especially in the Social Consultation Councils (consultative bodies of local administrations)

